hdr103606-bd.def: GNI per capita (2017 PPP International $, using natural logarithm) expressed as an index using a minimum value of $100 and a maximum value $75,000.
hdr103606-bd.name: Income index
hdr103606-bd.source: HDRO calculations based on GNI per capita (2017 PPP International $) from World Bank (2020a), World Development Indicators database. Accessed on 22 July 2020.

hdr123506-bd.def: Derived from the ratio of female to male wages, female and male shares of economically active population and gross national income (in 2017 purchasing power parity terms). See Technical note 3 at http://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/hdr2020_technical_notes.pdf for details.
hdr123506-bd.name: Estimated gross national income per capita
hdr123506-bd.source: HDRO calculations based on ILO (2020), UNDESA (2019a), World Bank (2020a), United Nations Statistics Division (2020b) and IMF (2020).

hdr123606-bd.def: Derived from the ratio of female to male wages, female and male shares of economically active population and gross national income (in 2017 purchasing power parity terms). See Technical note 3 at http://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/hdr2020_technical_notes.pdf for details.
hdr123606-bd.name: Estimated gross national income per capita
hdr123606-bd.source: HDRO calculations based on ILO (2020), UNDESA (2019a), World Bank (2020a), United Nations Statistics Division (2020b) and IMF (2020).

hdr183906-bd.def: Total compensation of employees, expressed as a percentage of GDP, which measures total output. Total compensation is the total remuneration, in cash or in kind, payable by an enterprise to an employee in return for work done by the employee during the accounting period.
hdr183906-bd.name: Labour share of GDP, comprising wages and social protection transfers
hdr183906-bd.source: ILO (2020). ILOSTAT database. https://ilostat.ilo.org/data/. Accessed 21 July 2020.

hdr194506-bd.def: Sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products, expressed in 2017 international dollars using purchasing power parity (PPP) rates.
hdr194506-bd.name: Gross domestic product (GDP), tota
hdr194506-bd.source: World Bank (2020a). World Development Indicators database. Washington, DC. http://data.worldbank.org. Accessed 22 July 2020.

hdr194906-bd.def: GDP in a particular period divided by the total population in the same period.
hdr194906-bd.name: GDP per capita
hdr194906-bd.source: World Bank (2020a). World Development Indicators database. Washington, DC. http://data.worldbank.org. Accessed 22 July 2020.

hdr195706-bd.def: Aggregate income of an economy generated by its production and its ownership of factors of production, less the incomes paid for the use of factors of production owned by the rest of the world, converted to international dollars using PPP rates, divided by midyear population.
hdr195706-bd.name: Gross national income (GNI) per capita
hdr195706-bd.source: World Bank (2020a), IMF (2020) and United Nations Statistics Division (2020b)

hdr65606-bd.def: Value of acquisitions of new or existing fixed assets by the business sector, governments and households (excluding their unincorporated enterprises) less disposals of fixed assets, expressed as a percentage of GDP. No adjustment is made for depreciation of fixed assets.
hdr65606-bd.name: Gross fixed capital formation
hdr65606-bd.source: World Bank (2020a). World Development Indicators database. Washington, DC. http://data.worldbank.org. Accessed 22 July 2020.
